constructor.details: OZ v5 Ownable requires the base constructor argument. Pass the initial owner at deployment time.

params.to: Recipient EOA/contract that will receive both tokens.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

swapExactIn(address,address,address,uint.details: OnlyOwner, nonReentrant. Approves just-in-time the router, then resets approval to 0.

params.amountOutMinimum: Minimum acceptable output (raw units) for slippage protection
params.router: Uniswap v3 router address (e.g., SwapRouter02 on Base)
params.tokenIn: Input token address (must be in the vault)

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

exitPositionAndWithdrawAll(address).notice: Close position (if any), move all funds to the vault, then transfer all vault balances to `to`.

setPoolOnce(address).notice: One-time set of the adapter (which implies pool/nfpm/gauge for this vault).

swapExactIn(address,address,address,uint.notice: Swap exact amountIn of tokenIn -> tokenOut via Uniswap v3 Router, keeping proceeds in the vault.
